<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="301" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[135,777,1181,1718]" pageId="3" pageNumber="301">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,246,1181,1205]" pageId="3" pageNumber="301">Remarks.</emphasis>
In the original description of the genus 
<taxonomicName authority=", Godwin-Austen, 1918" authorityName=", Godwin-Austen" authorityYear="1918" class="Gastropoda" family="Camaenidae" genus="Landouria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="3" pageNumber="301" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[657,769,1181,1205]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="301">Landouria</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Godwin-Austen HH" box="[136,373,1213,1237]" pageId="3" pageNumber="301" pagination="601 - 621" refId="ref3557" refString="Godwin-Austen HH (1918) Zoological results of the abor expedition, 1911 - 12. 49, Mollusca, 9. Records of the Indian Museum, 8: 601 - 621." type="journal article" year="1918">Godwin-Austen, 1918</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
included five species from 
<collectingCountry box="[670,775,1213,1237]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="3" pageNumber="301">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
and the Himalayas (northern and north-eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[699,762,1245,1269]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="301">India</collectingCountry>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Schileyko AA &amp; Kuznetsov AG" box="[137,490,1277,1301]" pageId="3" pageNumber="301" pagination="43 - 54" refId="ref4434" refString="Schileyko AA &amp; Kuznetsov AG (1998) Land snails of the genus Landouria Godwin-Austen, 1918 and some other Bradybaenidae of Nepal (Gastropoda, Pulmonata). Ruthenica, 8: 43 - 54." type="journal article" year="1998">Schileyko &amp; Kuznetsov (1998)</bibRefCitation>
added four species from 
<collectingCountry box="[136,203,1309,1333]" name="Nepal" pageId="3" pageNumber="301">Nepal</collectingCountry>
to the genus. Other species were described and reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[290,394,1341,1365]" name="Indonesia" pageId="3" pageNumber="301">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
and the 
<collectingCountry box="[485,608,1341,1365]" name="Philippines" pageId="3" pageNumber="301">Philippines</collectingCountry>
, and have often been mentioned as 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Godwin-Austen" authorityYear="1918" box="[348,461,1373,1397]" class="Gastropoda" family="Camaenidae" genus="Landouria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="3" pageNumber="301" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[348,461,1373,1397]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="301">Landouria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Rensch B" box="[477,628,1373,1397]" pageId="3" pageNumber="301" pagination="1 - 130" refId="ref4275" refString="Rensch B (1931) Die Molluskenfauna der Kleinen Sunda-Inseln Bali, Lombok, Sumbawa, Flores und Sumba. 2. Zoologisches Jahrbuch, 63, Abt. f. Syst: 1 - 130." type="book chapter" year="1931">Rensch, 1931</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Zilch A" box="[642,771,1373,1397]" pageId="3" pageNumber="301" pagination="293 - 319" refId="ref4901" refString="Zilch A (1966) Die Typen und Typoide des Naturmuseums Senckenberg, 35: Mollusca: Camaenidae (5). Archiv fur Molluskenkunde, 95: 293 - 319." type="journal article" year="1966">Zilch, 1966</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Marwoto RM" box="[136,305,1405,1429]" pageId="3" pageNumber="301" pagination="8 - 21" refId="ref3859" refString="Marwoto RM (2016) The occurrence of the terrestrial snail from Sumatra (Mollusca, Gastropoda). Zoo Indonesia, 25 (1): 8 - 21." type="journal article" year="2016">Marwoto, 2016</bibRefCitation>
). However, the systematic positions of these island taxa remain uncertain. By compiling distribution records, 
<bibRefCitation author="Schileyko AA &amp; Kuznetsov AG" box="[230,568,1469,1493]" pageId="3" pageNumber="301" pagination="43 - 54" refId="ref4434" refString="Schileyko AA &amp; Kuznetsov AG (1998) Land snails of the genus Landouria Godwin-Austen, 1918 and some other Bradybaenidae of Nepal (Gastropoda, Pulmonata). Ruthenica, 8: 43 - 54." type="journal article" year="1998">Schileyko &amp; Kuznetsov (1998)</bibRefCitation>
concluded that the genus is restricted to northern 
<collectingCountry box="[456,513,1501,1525]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="301">India</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[523,589,1501,1525]" name="Nepal" pageId="3" pageNumber="301">Nepal</collectingCountry>
, northern 
<collectingCountry box="[696,771,1502,1525]" name="Myanmar" pageId="3" pageNumber="301">Burma</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[180,288,1533,1557]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="3" pageNumber="301">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Godwin-Austen HH" box="[443,693,1533,1557]" pageId="3" pageNumber="301" pagination="601 - 621" refId="ref3557" refString="Godwin-Austen HH (1918) Zoological results of the abor expedition, 1911 - 12. 49, Mollusca, 9. Records of the Indian Museum, 8: 601 - 621." type="journal article" year="1918">Godwin-Austen (1918)</bibRefCitation>
, the Sri Lankan 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Jousseaume" baseAuthorityYear="1894" box="[225,332,1565,1589]" class="Gastropoda" family="Camaenidae" genus="Landouria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="3" pageNumber="301" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="radleyi">
<emphasis box="[225,332,1565,1589]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="301">L. radleyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
showed a short and oval flagellum with an elongated distal end with no sign of tubercles, which are characteristic of other 
<taxonomicName box="[422,626,1629,1653]" class="Gastropoda" family="Camaenidae" genus="Landouria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="3" pageNumber="301" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[422,535,1629,1653]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="301">Landouria</emphasis>
species.
</taxonomicName>
Therefore, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Jousseaume" baseAuthorityYear="1894" class="Gastropoda" family="Camaenidae" genus="Landouria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="3" pageNumber="301" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="radleyi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="301">L. radleyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
probably needs to be reclassified in another possibly undescribed genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
